<br>
<br>
As a warrior you'll notice when in small groups ie..<br>
You...Druid....Shaman or cleric...(2 in group) You'll want to do as much damage as possible the group will mainly rely on you to take the mob out...Unless it was mobs with say less that 1,000hp i always outdamaged the casters in the long run  here's a few tips on what 2hander to buy<br>
<br>
<br>
spend 30pp on a weighted axe....45dmg 150dly..most damage i have done with it was a double slash for 332dmg/ 132dmg..have the screen shot if you would like to see....as you might have noticed once your 2hs skill gets above 190 you'll begin to land tripple slashes..best tripple 210/165/170......now realize being a warrior you are in NO need of a bow..just dish out the 30pp for the weighted axe and pull with it...Ie open with it go hit the mob for the opening blow and watch its HP fall then run back to pull Loc and nail the mob again with the weighted...then as soon as the swing at pull loc is done switch to your primary weapons to finish the mob off....I got through lvl 35 in 5 hours in Iceclad useing this techneque and I didn't have a duel wield setup then ( Didn't have the pp to buy the right duel wield combo) <br>
<br>
<br>
2hander = opening blow( throw your bow away)<br>
And Str will increase the damage you can do enourmously if the str bonus on your items is +10 or more ....most str buffs from you buddies after lvl 30 will be for 25ish + so ALWAYS get the str buff ...you'll do alot more dmg =)<br>
<br>
just my 2cp</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR></TABLE></TD></TR></TABLE>